    <item>
      <title>MUD Client Downloads</title>
      <link>https://darkpawns.labz0rz.com/connect/client-downloads/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://darkpawns.labz0rz.com/connect/client-downloads/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;downloads&#34;&gt;downloads*&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Anything you could ever need to MUD.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;mud-clients&#34;&gt;mud clients&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;gmud-v19b-206kb&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.dp-players.com/download/download.php?file=0&#34;&gt;gMUD v1.9b&lt;/a&gt; (206kb)&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Your standard MUD client. Freeware, ANSI support, relatively small scrollback buffer,&#xA;trigger and alias support.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.dp-players.com/download/download.php?file=1&#34;&gt;MUSHClient v3.45&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;(1.35mb) -&#xA;One of the more feature-rich MUD clients available. Seemingly endless scrollback buffer;&#xA;this one seems to be more popular with the trigger-reliant mudders. This is&#xA;shareware, so the full program costs $20. Or you can use a &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.dp-players.com/go.php?dp=files/mushclient_serial.mud&#34;&gt;serial code&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
